                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    line-height: 1.5;">Another one based on true events, Spotlight hits hardest with clarity. It follows a team of Boston Globe reporters as they uncover the kind of story most people would rather not read: systemic abuse within the Catholic Church, buried for decades. It’s not dramatic, no stylized monologues, just methodical, unglamorous work done by people who understand the weight of getting it right. What makes it remarkable is how it doesn’t sensationalize or overplay the story; it trusts the facts to speak for themselves. </p>
